ic 1/2 done<br>Person B is level 54 he has his epic 1/2 done<br> <br>Epic loot drops: it should go to B based on level.<br><br>Again, the idea behind this is that level 49 will have his chance for his epic peice as well, as long as everyone participates in Epic Nights as an ongoing thing.  Even if we do a zone &amp; get only one epic peice for one person each Tuesday, its an accomplishment &amp; it's one less person that needs an item.<br><br>There is also an underlying theme here that I should mention. It's called selflessness, caring for your fellow Knight.  Wanting to see others get items &amp; excel as much as you do yourself.  I don't know about anyone else, but when Floggy &amp; Forgelin got their epics, it made ME feel good &amp; good for them.  Same as when Cornwalis received his title. Good for the Knights as a whole.<br><br>But again, this is just my opinion. I do hope others feel the same.<br><br>*hugs* <p></br><a href="http://angelfire.com/games3/TamzachShadowslayer" target="_blank"><img src="http://members.aol.com/blackmist2/tampost.jpg" border="0"></a> <BR>Tamzach Foxyone <BR>57th Season Preserver & Goddess of all things Huggable =)<BR>Knights of Valor<BR>Knight Distinguished<br><italic>Animo Et Fide!!</italic><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub55.ezboard.com/ubascomb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>bascomb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>KoV member</span><br>  Posts: 112<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(1/3/02 1:41:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub55.ezboard.com/fknightsofvalor76584frm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=42.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Tuesday Epic Nights for January ~~</span><hr size=1> Ok, how will we handle a situation like this:<br><br>A) Level 5