 a minimum, I have but one request to everyone: if you have a criticism please try to offer a viable alternative approach, such as what Bascomb saying.  Of course, we can't try all of them at once so once again please be patient as we go through the alternatives until we find one that is most satisfactory and can be applied uniformly.<br><br>Some commentary on Bascy's suggestion: you stated Honor System in the same breath as what amounts to a merit-based approach.  I don't see how Honor system looting would work here.  I'll use my Paw spires experience as a reference: one of the group member's starts looting corpses until either 3pp or a fine steel weapon is found; the same person loots multiple corpses if necessary until either of the conditions above is met.  Then the next person in alphabetical order follows the same procedure and the pattern repeats itself throughout the night.  No one checks for 3pp accuracy: it could be 5-50pp for all anyone really knows; it's up to the looter to be honest, hence the Honor System.  This system fails in the epic scenario since it becomes a point of contention as to who is the first to loot.<br><br>We could continue discussions of the merits of the Merit-based (ya, sorry about the pun), Roll-the-dice, and other approaches but this gets off-topic for this thread.<br><br>Important things to remember:<br>1) We all come out ahead when we work together<br>2) Trust is crucial to success<br> <p><IMG src="http://www.battle.net/images/battle/diablo2exp/images/animations/bestiary/act3/zakarumpriest.gif"><BR>Badorin<BR>55 Preserver<BR>Knight Ambassador, Knights of Valor<BR>Alt Rep to Grey Coalition<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub55.ezboard.com/ubascomb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>bascomb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>KoV member</span><br>  Posts: 117<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(1/4/02 1:10:00 pm)</font><br>   <a 