it clear to avoid confusion at that critical moment that some rare drop is decaying while we hash out who loots.  It is my opinion that the looting rights should be established before the drop to avoid confusion at the time.<br><br>I am in an enviable position being the highest level wizard in KoV.  I am close to completion of my Epic.  There are a series of time consuming events that only involve spending a few kPP and porting to get to the point of needing to get three staffs.  <br><br>The Staff of Gabstik - <br>Loot the oil from the spawned (triggered) Enraged Golem in Plane of fear and turn it in to Kandim Firepot in and he gives you the staff<br><br>I have this staff<br><br>The Gnarled Staff -<br>Drops occassionaly from Venril Sathir (25% approx)<br><br>I need<br><br>The Blue Crystal Staff -<br>Drops from Phinigal Atropolis in Kedge (10% approx)<br><br>I need<br><br>Once I have these three staffs in my possession it is a matter of travel to complete the acquisition of my Staff of Four, the forth staff being supplied by Arantir in Everfrost to comlete the making of the powerful combination of four staffs.<br><br>Using the wizzie epic as an example, it seems reasonable to let those who have one or more staffs to loot the ones needed to allow at least one of us to have that Epic.  To have me in possession of the SoG and the BCS in another wizard's hand and the GS in another makes little sense to me.  It is easy for me to feel this way, I must admit, considering my situation.  Then again Langley was created in Oct of 1999 so he could hardly be accused of being a powerleveller.  It may have been too much time spent helping others?  Or maybe just lazy LOL.<br><br>Another note is that the Epics were implemented with the RoK and at the same time the level limit was extended to 60 from 50.  Is this relevant?  I think it is, the Epics being something to accomplish with the higher levels.  They are Epic.  One thing mentioned was that is someone being punished for slow levelling because time was spent working on their epic?  My feeling is the time would have been better spent working on those said levels and getting experience in the higher end game before allotting time to getting their epic.  That is only my opinion though.  If we are not honest we are doomed.  Honesty is the KEY to anything working and should not be questioned.  Selflessness is also an attribute that is imperative for success.<br><br>Lang     <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub55.ezboard.com/ubascomb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>bascomb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>KoV member</span><br>  Posts: 118<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(1/4/02 4:12:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub55.ezboard.com/fknightsofvalor76584frm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=42.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Tuesday Epic Nights for January ~~</span><hr size=1> To Answer Lang's Question - <br><br>ABSOLUTELY.  Levels are a definate plus - <br><br>I'm with Lang and Bado on this, I don't want rules, but a sure fire understanding of what is going/needs to happen is always there.  The more of us that understand, the more can help someone that is upset about not getting a drop understand what's happening.  <br><br>As far as Lang's Epic, I'm with you bro - you have 2 pieces, to give one of the others to JoeShmoe when you're at the raid/event is dumb.  <br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub55.ezboard.com/utamzachshadowslayer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tamzach Shadowslayer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight Distinguished</span><br>  Posts: 160<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(1/5/02 12:15:07 pm)</font><br>