 they want, but it does stand to reason that we should not come to totally trivialize the respect that the &quot;elders&quot; of our perspective classes deserve.  In example, I can tell you that I used to do lots of quests and I worked on my Soulfire quest from lvl 4 all the way up to lvl 48 before it was finally realized and I held Soulfire in my hand for the first time.  I worked for and dreamed of that day for ages and many levels and many other highlights in my growing up as a Paladin, and it really meant something to me to finally achieve that pinnacle.  The next week, I was in Highkeep hunting with Katalayna and a zone shout came up stating, &quot;Lvl 22 Paladin with Soulfire LFG&quot;.   I still cannot describe exactly the way that this affected me and trivialized in a way all that I had worked for and I had to camp out.  I was confused, upset and, yes, angry...it was not jealousy or pride that got me feeling this way, but the thoughts of how many levels I had worked and fought and savored the moment of achieving my goal.  I thought to myself...How could a lvl 22 really appreciate the full meaning of acquiring such a Holy weapon, what would they have to work towards and be proud of, and how it looked for my class in particular that now could put our long-coveted achievement in the hands of a Paladin who might very well have only been playing that character for a mere matter of hours...it bursted my bubble, I don't mind admitting.  All I am saying is..give honor and respect and due course to those who have been working for their epics and other goals for possibly a dozen levels or more...cheer them on, be there to support them and let us all work together to boost all of our members and our guild in this fine way and we will all be just that much stronger for it=)<br><br> I really like the way this thread has panned out and feel that having a central person in charge of making the call on our objective on these nights can alieviate a lot of concern.  With Tam in charge of making that ultimate decision, I am confidant that we all know the fairness and commitment that she exibits and can trust that she will look out for the best interests of all concerned, and it gives those of us going on the raid the peace of mind to participate without worry or hard feelings, as we know that someday we shall be looked out for also.  We have our NBG policy and the guidelines have been set down here for how these epic nights will go with concern to loot management.  If you need an item in a particular zone that we are raiding for epic or otherwise, take the initiative to let Tam or other leader know...they can only make the best and fairest judgment when they have all of the facts, so don't be shy to speak up and let them know in tell because no one can guess or keep track of who is sitting where in their quests.  Above all, let's go and have a great time, support, encourage, and cheer on our family members...that is so much more important in the whole scheme of things than anything else...what is an epic or any other goal achievement worth if you do not have those who you love and admire to share it with?)'  Animo et Fide and love to all!=) <p><center><img src="http://www.avvisione.com/members/LL.jpg"></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub55.ezboard.com/utamzachshadowslayer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tamzach Shadowslayer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight Distinguished</span><br>  Posts: 164<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(1/7/02 11:09:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub55.ezboard.com/fknightsofvalor76584frm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=42.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Tuesday Epic Nights for January ~~</span><hr size=1> So well said Kitaqua. Your words of wisdom